and my wife is waiting.

14:45.177 --> 14:49.014
You have a wi...
Won... Wonderful show to see?

14:49.014 --> 14:50.390
Guilty. <i>Ciao</i>.

14:54.728 --> 14:56.522
You'd best get
your mind right, son!

14:56.522 --> 14:58.857
The game is the game,
and there ain't no winners.

14:58.941 --> 15:01.944
How many retired
gangbangers you know?

15:01.944 --> 15:03.862
Exactly.

15:07.950 --> 15:09.910
Barney...

15:09.910 --> 15:10.994
check it out.

15:11.078 --> 15:12.538
I found my scrapbook
from the old days.

15:12.538 --> 15:13.622
We're kind of busy
right now, Warren.

15:13.622 --> 15:15.207
We're scaring kids
straight, so...

15:15.207 --> 15:16.333
- No, no.
- Barney was

15:16.333 --> 15:18.585
the youngest member
of our Magic Enthusiasts Club

15:18.669 --> 15:20.295
years back.

15:20.379 --> 15:22.089
Famous for
escaping from handcuffs.

15:22.089 --> 15:23.298
Handcuffs, huh?

15:23.382 --> 15:24.383
Very tiny hands.

15:24.383 --> 15:26.552
That was his secret.

15:26.552 --> 15:28.637
See you around, baby hands.

15:30.013 --> 15:33.851
So, you don't know the bailiff
because you were a badass.

15:33.851 --> 15:36.770
You knew him because you guys
were in a nerd club together.

15:36.854 --> 15:40.607
Where you dazzled audiences
with your sleight-of-tiny-hand.

15:40.691 --> 15:43.735
So I was a late hand bloomer!

15:43.819 --> 15:45.612
Go ahead, laugh,

15:45.696 --> 15:47.114
laugh like all the others,

15:47.114 --> 15:50.617
but those magicians pulled off
the greatest trick of all:

15:50.701 --> 15:52.953
they accepted me.

15:54.955 --> 15:56.707
Okay, well,
to be fair,

15:56.707 --> 15:59.543
