slightly exaggerated

15:59.543 --> 16:01.837
my badass story, too.

16:03.005 --> 16:05.549
Oh, sorry. Uh, no,
thank you, housekeeping.

16:05.549 --> 16:06.717
I've already made my bed.

16:06.717 --> 16:10.929
And I only used
one washcloth, so it's...

16:11.013 --> 16:12.848
Congratulations,
Miss Sparkles.

16:12.848 --> 16:15.267
On behalf
of the Manitoba Hotel

16:15.267 --> 16:18.020
and Curling Rink Association,
we'd like to thank you

16:18.020 --> 16:21.648
for being the nicest, most
well-behaved hotel guest ever.

16:21.732 --> 16:23.984
Oh, yippee!

16:23.984 --> 16:25.903
What a loser!

16:25.903 --> 16:27.571
Your story's not true,
either, is it, Ted?

16:27.571 --> 16:30.365
Not at all.

16:30.449 --> 16:32.826
Make sure you get
my good side, Princess!

16:35.746 --> 16:37.456
I left the courthouse that day

16:37.456 --> 16:40.792
questioning what
I was even doing with my life...

16:40.876 --> 16:43.128
and then that night,
I had a dream.

16:43.212 --> 16:45.214
Sorry I failed, son.

16:45.214 --> 16:47.799
What about your
Pebble Theory, Dad?

16:47.883 --> 16:50.636
One good deed ripples out
and makes another and another?

16:50.636 --> 16:53.180
Yeah.

16:53.180 --> 16:54.598
This is what really happens

16:54.598 --> 16:57.518
when you throw a pebble
into Frog Lake.

17:01.980 --> 17:04.066
The truth is,
you can fight

17:04.066 --> 17:07.486
your whole life to do good
and still get nowhere.

17:07.486 --> 17:08.612
You're wrong.

17:08.612 --> 17:11.114
Some good's gonna ripple
out of this, Dad.

17:11.198 --> 17:13.158
I promise.

17:15.661 --> 17:17.788
Great, I've angered the Frog King.

17:19.665 --> 17:23.210
Later that night,
some good did ripple out.

17:24.545 --> 17:27.089
Hey.

17:27.089 --> 17:29.091
What, are you here to gloat?

17:29.091 --> 17:32.219
